        "description": "The Electrode Store is a leading US-based manufacturer and distributor who designs, develops, manufactures, and distributes high quality electrodiagnostic (EDX) neuro supplies including disposable needle electrodes, re-usable and disposable surface electrodes and related equipment and supplies for electromyography (EMG), nerve conduction studies (NCS or NCV), electroencephalography (EEG) and intraoperative neurophysiological monitoring (IONM).Products include handheld nerve conduction test systems, monopolar and concentric needle electrodes, hypodermic needles for EMG-guided botulinum toxin injections, subdermal needle electrodes, surface electrodes including a variety of disposable (hydrogel) adhesive electrodes, EEG electrode caps, stim (stimulation) probes, plus electrode gels, pastes and more. The Electrode Store and global partner Alera MedTech recently acquired the DPNCheck product line from NeuroMetrix.  DPNCheck is a fast, accurate, and quantitative nerve conduction test that is used to evaluate systemic neuropathies such as diabetic peripheral neuropathy (DPN). It is designed to be quickly and easily used by clinicians at the point-of-care, to objectively detect, stage, and monitor peripheral neuropathies such as those associated with diabetes.  The device measures nerve conduction velocity and response amplitude of the sural nerve (a nerve in the lower leg and ankle). Users may include nurses, techs (technologists or technicians), service providers, or physicians including neurologists, endocrinologists and other diabetes specialists, podiatrists, oncologists, general practitioners, and other clinicians.We have competitive prices, with easy and quick ordering by website, phone, or email.  We are seeking distributors in countries outside of the United States.",
