        "description": "Visit the Michigan Booth in the USA PavilionHall 16, Stand 16F17-1 Active ManufacturingActive Manufacturing is an ISO-certified prototype and short-run contract manufacturer specializing in tight-tolerance stampings, clips, and assemblies—from miniature foil components to parts up to 45 inches square. With in-house capabilities including mechanical, hydraulic, and servo presses; multi-axis fiber and CO₂ laser cutting; wire EDM; advanced machining; and robotic, laser, MIG, and TIG welding, we provide full inspection and quality assurance. We help companies bring innovative designs from concept through prototype and short-run production, ready for high-volume manufacturing. www.activemfg.net Jeff Miller, +1 616.842.0800, jeff.miller@activemfg.net  ENDOCORPENDOCORP is the largest global supplier of OEM Olympus endoscopy parts to ISO-certified repair facilities. With over 1 million parts in stock and almost 30 years of experience, ENDOCORP delivers fast, reliable support for flexible endoscope repairs. Headquartered in Southfield, Michigan, ENDOCORP offers unmatched inventory, technical expertise, and OEM-quality solutions—empowering endoscopy service centers worldwide. www.endocorpusa.com Rhonda Stroud, +1 586.894.3018, sales@endocorpusa.com  Everis MedicalEveris is committed to delivering leading medical products and continuously evolving to meet the needs of healthcare providers like you. With over a century of combined experience in the medical device industry, our team remains dedicated to providing advanced devices and technology essential for exceptional patient care. We are focused on supporting your success and enhancing patient outcomes every step of the way. Everis provides innovative solutions like the Shaw Scalpel®, Biodesign® grafts, and advanced tools for Sialendoscopy - all designed to empower physicians and enhance patient care. This well-rounded portfolio allows us to serve a broad range of healthcare professionals while staying deeply connected to the needs of ENT physicians.www.everismedical.comMiles Williams, +1 269.888.1191, mwilliams@everismedical.com  in2being in2being is a medical device development and regulatory service provider located near Ann Arbor, Michigan. We combine in-house U.S.-FDA regulatory expertise and technical development expertise to assist at all project stages. in2being’s deep expertise with the U.S. FDA allows us to help foreign companies conform their products to the expectations of the U.S. market. www.in2being.com Gene Parunak, +1 844.622.3464, info@in2being.com  Oxus America, Inc.Oxus is an engineering, manufacturing, and service company specializing in medical devices and gas separation technology. We design and manufacture products in Auburn Hills, Michigan. As an ISO 13485 certified, FDA-registered OEM supplier, Oxus offers high quality key service parts for portable and stationary oxygen concentrators. www.oxusamerica.com Gary Abusamra, +1 248.798.8335, gabusamra@oxusamerica.com ROSS ControlsROSS manufactures a line of standard pneumatic miniature valves and custom solutions for Medical Industry applications including oxygen concentrators, therapeutic support, intermittent compression, and medical beds. ROSS products are recognized around the world for reliability, repeatability, and robust design, using a proven ROSS/FLEX® process to help define specific pneumatic control needs and develop turnkey pneumatic solutions specific for each medical application. ROSS Controls (ROSS) has manufacturing and sales operations throughout the world including in Europe where ROSS is located in Germany, France, Poland, and the U.K. www.rosscontrols.com Jay Dalal, +1 248.764.1832, jay.dalal@rosscontrols.com  SSI Electronics, Inc.SSI Electronics/SSI Medical is a leader in custom electrodes supporting remote patient monitoring such as Holter or extended wear ECG/EKG, EEG monitoring, and EMG and NMES applications. With ISO-13485 manufacturing capabilities, in-house engineering, and over 40 years of manufacturing experience, SSI has earned its reputation as the USA’s go-to custom electrode partner. www.ssi-electronics.com Dave Kerkstra, +1 616.866.8880, davek@ssi-electronics.com  Symbiote, Inc.Symbiote has been designing and building innovative laboratories for over 40 years, serving healthcare, life sciences, hardware development, and R&D. More than lab furniture, we create adaptable, future-ready spaces that evolve with your research needs. From vision to reality, our team guides you in building smarter, flexible labs that support growth and innovation. As we expand globally, Symbiote continues to empower research and development teams worldwide with cutting-edge solutions. www.symbiote.com Barrett Randolph, +1 616.772.1790, brandolph@symbiote.com",
