        "description": "StaClear: The First Low-Particulate Ophthalmic Syringe TRUSTED BY RETINA SPECIALISTS Now approved for sale in the European Union! All 3 StaClear Single-Use Syringes for Eye Injection: Attached Needle Syringe, Luer Slip Syringe, Luer Lock Syringe  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ \"Excellent marking and smooth action — excellent choice delivering intravitreal agents!\" – Dr. Yugen Wang, MD, Oregon Retina Center  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ StaClear Syringes are designed for: Ophthalmologists Outsourcing Facilities & Compounding Pharmacies Ophthalmic Drug Companies StaClear Offers 3 Types of Fillable Single-Use Intravitreal Syringes: Attached Needle Luer Lock Luer Slip One box contains 100 syringes. 2 Trays Per Box. — StaClear Luer Lock is now also available in Unit Packs — *Ophthalmic injections must use a needle indicated for ophthalmic use.  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ “Our syringe rejection rate went down dramatically with the StaClear syringes. This saves us money, time, and headaches from a Quality perspective. StaClear is a top-tier product.” - Mike Basista, R.Ph., Pharm.D., BCSCP, Supervising Pharmacist, RC Outsourcing  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ WHY INVENT AN INTRAVITREAL SYRINGE? The Backstory Behind the Invention of StaClear StaClear has 100x fewer particles than generic syringes lubricated with silicone oil.  Its patented technology is a lubricant coating anchored to the walls of the syringe (versus liquid silicone oil in generic syringes that has been linked to adverse outcomes). 5 REASONS WHY RETINA SURGEONS CHOOSE STACLEAR FOR DRUG DELIVERY REASON #1: PRECISION DOSING Retina specialists inject very small amounts of drug in the eye. We designed our syringes to suit their precise dosing needs. REASON #2: OPTIMIZED DESIGN All 3 StaClear Syringes (Attached Needle, Luer Lock & Luer Slip) are designed to reduce dead space, saving up to $10-15 of drug wastage. REASON #3: CONTROLLED INJECTION EXPERIENCE Elastomer piston ensures sealing integrity, mitigating a known risk in silicone-free syringes. REASON #4: IMPROVED ACCURACY StaClear Syringes offer better dosing accuracy than 1mL syringe types. #REASON 5: OPHTHALMIC-SAFE MATERIALS Meets chemical and biocompatibility standards for ophthalmic use.  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ \"The StaClear syringe provides consistent dosage and a smooth injection experience. Very easy to use and work with!\" – Dr. Alan Sheyman, MD, New York Eye and Retina  ------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ The National Eye Institute (through its SBIR grant program) at the NIH championed this important research. Thanks to its support, StaClear is the first low-particulate intravitreal syringe designed, developed, and commercialized via the SBIR program to serve the needs of the ophthalmic industry. Meet us at our booth: 📍 Hall 16 / F11-1 to see our syringes and also learn about our contract manufacturing services for your own medical devices.",
